{"parse":{"title":"Berkley Center for Religion, Peace, and World Affairs","pageid":12311883,"revid":781779875,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:BerkleyCenter_Logo.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d5/BerkleyCenter_Logo.jpg/300px-BerkleyCenter_Logo.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"129\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d5/BerkleyCenter_Logo.jpg/450px-BerkleyCenter_Logo.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d5/BerkleyCenter_Logo.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"480\" data-file-height=\"207\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:BerkleyCenter_Logo.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Logo of the Berkley Center for Religion, Peace, and World Affairs at Georgetown University</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Berkley Center for Religion, Peace, and World Affairs</b> is an academic research center at <a href=\"/wiki/Georgetown_University\" title=\"Georgetown University\">Georgetown University</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Washington,_DC\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Washington, DC\">Washington, DC</a> dedicated to the interdisciplinary study of <a href=\"/wiki/Religion\" title=\"Religion\">religion</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Ethics\" title=\"Ethics\">ethics</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Politics\" title=\"Politics\">politics</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The center was founded in 2006<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> under a gift from <a href=\"/wiki/W._R._Berkley\" title=\"W. R. Berkley\">William R. Berkley</a>, a member of Georgetown's Board of Directors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-IGGprofile_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-IGGprofile-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The center's founding director was  Thomas Banchoff.<sup id=\"cite_ref-IGGprofile_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-IGGprofile-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Berkley_Center_for_Religion,_Peace,_and_World_Affairs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://berkleycenter.georgetown.edu/about\">\"About Us &#124; Berkley Center for Religion, Peace, and World Affairs &#124; Georgetown University\"</a>. Berkleycenter.georgetown.edu<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2012-02-04</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=About+Us+%26%23124%3B+Berkley+Center+for+Religion%2C+Peace%2C+and+World+Affairs+%26%23124%3B+Georgetown+University&amp;rft.pub=Berkleycenter.georgetown.edu&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fberkleycenter.georgetown.edu%2Fabout&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABerkley+Center+for+Religion%2C+Peace%2C+and+World+Affairs\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Carol Zimmerman for <i>The Boston Pilot</i>. April 11, 2016. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thebostonpilot.com/article.asp